Sutphin Boulevard, west side, opposite One Hundred Twenty-second Ave., showing the Oscar S. Williams house of 1873. Other owners or inhabitants were J. Murray 1896; L. Dunham; and William Sweezy, son-in-law of O.S. Williams, who removed to the vicinity of Three Mile Mill which he operated. It was demolished in 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

April 1925.
